During a visit to the Pentagon, Vice President Kamala Harris expressed gratitude and support for the military personnel. She acknowledged the challenges they face and commended their dedication and sacrifice. Harris emphasized the importance of their work in the face of global threats to climate, health, physical security, and cybersecurity. She assured them that the President and she stood with them and recognized their role in ensuring the nation's security and success. Harris praised the leadership of Secretary Austin and Chairman Milley, as well as the Commander-in-Chief's respect for the military. She also highlighted the significance of Black History Month and honored the contributions of black soldiers throughout American history. Harris concluded by recounting a personal encounter with a soldier's mother, expressing her gratitude for the service of all military members.